snippet.textDisplay:
As I read the English captions of this song, I realise that this song is a true testament to the beauty of the Urdu language and it's words. There is so much power and depth to the words that just 3-4 of them have the ability to fully convey an entire set of circumstances and visualise the narrator's feelings in the mind of one who understands Urdu. And yet, entire sentences are needed to deliver just a watered down version of it in English and other languages.

Absolutely beautiful, the singers, the musicians, the set, the entire team, and most of all, Urdu!
